tweet: Day by Jay #9: We live on the slippery slope by @jaydimonte  https://t.co/REi4ZpyHoU

name: Guy Turner
tweet: END/ In the meantime, if yesterday felt distracting, sad and unproductive, you are not alone. Today will be better, and tomorrow too.

name: Guy Turner
tweet: 7/ ...or risk permanently splintering what many generations worked so hard to leave us. It is time to bare our soul as a country.   I am not yet sure how I will personally get involved in this - but I welcome ideas.

name: Guy Turner
tweet: 6/ My hope is that there are immediate political and legal consequences - we shall see. While I was long of the mind of "let's just get this behind us", I now feel we must transparently pursue the legal and political ramifications of every misstep that led us here...

name: Guy Turner
tweet: 5/  ...of democracy that is so often cited.  That means there must be consequences for what we witnessed yesterday, in the past two months and at times through the past four years. If not, the fringes will progressively consume the mainstream.

name: Guy Turner
tweet: 4/ ... prosperity (though they are oftentimes imperfectly shared). When enough people decide to eschew that social contract - led by our most elevated leader - law enforcement is overwhelmed because we are not a police state and don't want to be. Therein lies the fragility...

name: Guy Turner
tweet: 3/ What is fully behind that door is not pretty.  A new beginning in 13 days offers hope, but it doesn't in itself douse burning embers. A democratic society is a "social contract", where we tacitly agree to live by the rules for the resulting benefits of peace and...

name: Guy Turner
tweet: 2/ ...of trends that have seemed obvious for some time. Yet my hope is that in witnessing this crescendo through the smallest sliver of an opening door, the "mainstream" politicians who have more recently decided to wade into this bloody river will strive for shore.

name: Guy Turner
tweet: On Yesterday: 1/ We should all share in the dismay and anger over yesterday regardless of our "politics". Peace and the rights granted by the constitutions to all citizens - not just the loudest or most violent - transcend all politics. For me, yesterday witnessed a crescendo...

name: Guy Turner
tweet: So, if I smell like a pig.... N/N

name: Guy Turner
tweet: Here is the recipe: Coconut oil: 120 grams (added so that it lathers better) Pig lard: 475 grams Distilled water: 226 grams Lye (NaOH): 85 grams Fragrance: 18 grams (I used mint) Coloring: I used green food coloring in half the batch (pour in parallel). Turned red!?!?!? 6/N

name: Guy Turner
tweet: Stays in there for 24 hours. Then you un-mold, cut as desired and let cure for a month or so. You can handle it with bare hands after 24 hrs, since the lye should be completely reacted. But aging it dries some of the water out, and constitutes the bar more solidly. 5/N

name: Guy Turner
tweet: Then you pour it in some sort of mold. This is one made from an old cardboard cracker box. I made fun lines with a fork on the top. 5/N  https://t.co/1xipYioMA5

name: Guy Turner
tweet: Then mix it all together when both fats and lye solution are around 110F, and beat with a stick blender until it forms a "trace". My recipe is 5% superfatted, meaning there is 5% more fat than the lye can react, so leaves skin soft with the extra fat. I don't mind pig. 4/N

name: Guy Turner
tweet: Then you mix lye with water. The lye solution "saponifies" the fat... turns it to soap. Lye is very dangerous and can turn you into soap too, hence the gloves and glasses. This is me measuring the distilled water before adding lye. 3/N  https://t.co/nPKmxRFt8r

name: Guy Turner
tweet: It started with my more than occasional bacon habit. ~5 lbs over two months yielded about a lb of rendered pig lard. Rendered means boiled with water 3-4+ times to purify. This is the settled lard over water after one such boil. +cutest daughter ever 2/N  https://t.co/7jZ27b9UXc

name: Guy Turner
tweet: Soap has taken on a new meaning with COVID, so I indulged in my very occasional hobby of cold process soap making. 1/N  https://t.co/iRsyR7GWE1
